.NET Framework 4.0.name: RandomPassword
.NET Framework 4.0.summary: This class can generate random passwords, which do not include ambiguous characters, such as I, l, and 1. The generated password will be made of 7-bit ASCII symbols. Every four characters will include one lower case character, one upper case character, one number, and one special symbol (such as '%') in a random order. The password will always start with an alpha-numeric character; it will not start with a special symbol (we do this because some back-end systems do not like certain special characters in the first position).

methods.name: Generate()
methods.remarks: The length of the generated password will be determined at random. It will be no shorter than the minimum default and no longer than maximum default.

methods.name: Generate(int length)
methods.summary: Generates a random password of the exact length.

methods.name: Generate(int minLength, int maxLength)
methods.remarks: The length of the generated password will be determined at random and it will fall with the range determined by the function parameters.
methods.syntax: public static string Generate(int minLength, int maxLength)
